name: (KlokGen) Fire Emblem-Style Character Generator
description:
This is a carefully trained and tagged model that can replicate the exact visual style of Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance and Radiant Dawn character artwork. It is also quite good at creating Gameboy-insertable spritesheets, though to do so, you will need to follow the guide image shown above.

Join the Fire Emblem Resource Repository Discord to get tips and talk to excellent spriters on how to fix up your images for use in Romhacks.

This Lora REQUIRES the use of Umi AI's Macross Ultimate model. This Lora was trained on Macross Ultimate and will have the best results with it!

This model is capable of replicating the FE6/7/8 and FE9/FE10 visual styles. Remember to prompt it according to the guide image linked above. Ask on the Discord if you don't understand what's going wrong.

If you wish to create nsfw content with this Lora, please instead refer to the Umi AI Discord, which is my main AI server.

Future plans:
Fire Emblem Awakening Portraits

Fire Emblem Fates Portraits

Fire Emblem Three Houses Portraits

Fire Emblem Engage Portraits

And more!

modelVersions.name: KlokGen Ethical v1.1
modelVersions.description:
This is a directly improved model over v1 of KlokGen Ethical. This model is capable, as before, of creating halfbodies and quarterbodies.

However, v1.1 introduces the ability to specify FE9-Style for your halfbodies, as well as FE10-Style. Currently, FE10-Style looks a little fucky, but that will be fixed later when I upload the FE10-Specific model, as well as the Halfbody-Only model.

Additionally, you can use Tellius-Style to create a mixed style of FE9 and FE10, as shown in the example images.

Quarterbodies and the dataset in general has been improved a bit. Remember, if you use a keyword like "Ike \(Fire Emblem\)", you will be able to gen based on that character's general appearance. If that character has a specific Danbooru tag, their data may also be added from Danbooru and this Lora combined. Lyn, is a good example, as she is a popular character on Danbooru.

For those popular character, use their specific game name. "Lyn \(Fire Emblem: Blazing Blade\)" will have better results than "Lyn \(Fire Emblem\)".

I will be posting single-style and dual-style Loras over the next few hours. They will be even better at replicating their specific styles than this unified Lora!

This model works best with Macross Ultimate. Run the Lora at 0.8 strength.

modelVersions.name: KlokGen Quarterbodies ONLY v1.1
modelVersions.description:
This model is for Quarterbodies only. These are the most finicky type of FE gens, and as such, they require specific settings to look good. My team is struggling to improve them, but our preferred settings are:

Use the Macross Ultimate model from this page.
DPM++ SDE at 15 Steps, 512x512, CFG 4
If you have Umi AI installed, you can use these negatives to improve the art style:

lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, text, error, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, out of focus, censorship, (multiple boys, multiple characters, multiple girls, multiple views:1.2), boobplate, NEGS Bad Artist Anime by nick-x-hacker, NEGS Bad Artist OG by nick-x-hacker, NEGS Easy Negative

And finally, this is a good starting prompt to try out:
